FEEDBACK:

CompletableFuture.supplyAsync on a Blocking Redis Call:
    supplyAsync without an explicit executor uses the common ForkJoinPool, which is sized for CPU-bound work.
    If your Redis call inside rotateRefreshToken is synchronous/blocking, you're blocking a ForkJoinPool thread —
    that's a problem under load. Either pass a dedicated executor:

    -   CompletableFuture.supplyAsync(() -> tokenService.rotateRefreshToken(refreshToken), ioExecutor)